Minister of Employment and Labour Minister Thulas Nxesi. JOHANNESBURG - Minister of Employment and Labour, Thulas Nxesi has tested positive for COVID-19. READ: Gauteng Premier tests positive for COVID-19 According to a statement released on Friday, Nxesi is self-isolation at home. "Minister Nxesi is in self-isolation and will continue working from home. All members of the office of the minister, who have come in contact with him will also undergo testing," read the statement. Nxesi is the 5th member of the executive to test positive for COVID-19.  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.